---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const awards = [
  'First Prize, International Chopin Piano Competition (2018)',
  'Avery Fisher Career Grant (2019)',
  'Gramophone Award for Best Instrumental Recording (2021)',
  'Royal Philharmonic Society Young Artist Award (2022)',
];
---

<Layout title="Bio â€” Elena Vasquez" description="Biography of concert pianist Elena Vasquez.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="section-title">Biography</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bio-section">
    <div class="container bio-grid">
      <div class="bio-image">
        <img
          src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594897030264-ab7d87efc473?w=800&q=80"
          alt="Elena Vasquez at the piano"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="bio-text">
        <p>
          Born in Buenos Aires to a family of musicians, Elena Vasquez began her
          piano studies at the age of five under the guidance of her grandmother,
          a former student of Martha Argerich. By sixteen, she had already performed
          as a soloist with the Buenos Aires Philharmonic.
        </p>
        <p>
          Elena went on to study at the Juilliard School in New York, where she
          worked closely with renowned pedagogue Emanuel Ax. Her breakthrough came
          in 2018 when she won First Prize at the International Chopin Piano
          Competition in Warsaw, captivating audiences with what the jury described
          as "an interpretation of extraordinary poetry and intelligence."
        </p>
        <p>
          Since then, Elena has performed with leading orchestras around the world,
          including the Berlin Philharmonic, London Symphony Orchestra, and the
          New York Philharmonic. Her recordings of the complete Chopin Nocturnes
          and Debussy's Preludes have been met with widespread critical acclaim.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beyond the concert stage, Elena is passionate about music education. She
          regularly gives masterclasses at conservatories across Europe and South
          America, and founded the Vasquez Foundation, which provides scholarships
          to young pianists from underrepresented communities.
        </p>
        <p>
          Elena currently divides her time between Amsterdam and Buenos Aires. When
          not touring, she can be found exploring the city's art galleries or
          cooking traditional Argentine cuisine for friends.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section awards-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Awards & Recognition</h2>
      <ul class="awards-list">
        {awards.map(award => (
          <li>{award}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .bio-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .bio-image img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .bio-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .awards-section {
    background: #F3F0EB;
  }

  .awards-list {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .awards-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .awards-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .bio-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .bio-image img {
      aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    }
  }
</style>
